ABOUT
Bumpas 349 was established February of 2018 and is sure to be a Tallahassee local favorite. Bumpas is a great place to relax and have a bite and drinks with friends, to catch your favorite sports event at the bar, or to enjoy a lunch or dinner outing with the family. Located in the old Calico Jack’s location in the heart of Capital Circle Northeast, Bumpas is also a favorite with the after-work crowd. Come by and see for yourself; in the meantime, check out some of our recent reviews below.
Welcoming and Friendly Atmosphere
"We loved the food and the selection. Very impressed with the beer station and selection. Welcoming and friendly atmosphere to hang out."
Peter Cruz
Great Flavor and Generous Portions
"
Came in on soft openings. We had Cobb salad and rib appetizer.  Great
 flavor and generous portions. Looking forward to full menu."
Greg Verhagen
Great Casual Atmosphere
"So friendly, great casual atmosphere, yummy food, great beer! We will be back! Added bonus: on the way home from home depot."
Jean Young
